You need to add:

#include <netinet/in.h>

to the list of includes in the right order:

#include <string.h>
#include <sys/types.h>
#include <sys/socket.h>
#include <netdb.h>
#include <errno.h>
#include <netinet/in.h> /* LOOK HERE! */
#include <arpa/inet.h>
#include "safecalls.h"

Then that error will go away, but you'll have to fix the other problems 
before it will compile.

Joe
